<HL>
   UNC Unit Gets Contracts
</HL>
<DATE>
09/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   UNC
</CO>
<IN>
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- UNC Inc. said its UNC Support Services
unit received three military contracts valued at about $183
million over the next 15 years.
   The company won a U.S. Navy contract for on-site support
and maintenance of 140 TH-57 helicopters and equipment. The
contract is for $28.6 million in the first year, and about
$28.2 million annually in the following three years.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   UNC Support Services also won a five-year, $7 million
simulator-instructor training contract from the U.S. Air
Force. The award has four one-year options, at a value of
about $1.3 million per year.
   In addition, UNC Support Services will be part of a team
to work on the Air Force's Special Operations Forces Aircrew
Training System program in Akron, Ohio. The 15-year contract
is worth about $65 million.
   UNC services aircraft engines and components, manufactures
jet engine parts and provides other services to the aviation
industry.
</TEXT>
